The paper deals with visual question answering, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The dataset introduced in the paper focuses on exploiting high-level semantic information present in images as textual cues, which involves reasoning and generating appropriate answers, indicating the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new evaluation metric that accounts for shortcomings of the text recognition module, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR).
